										<div>
						<h2>1.
Fashion Babylon, by Imogen Edwards-Jones</h2>
						
						
<p><a href="/tags/topic/Imogen+Edwards-Jones" target="_self" class="inform_link">Imogen Edwards-Jones</a> takes the reader through six months in the life of an anonymous British fashion designer in &quot;Fashion Babylon.&quot; Based on Edward-Jones's interviews with and investigations of real fashion designers, this novel is bursting with juicy tidbits about the secret, messy lives of the big-name designers. After reading this book, you will never flip through an issue of <a href="/tags/topic/Vogue+Magazine" target="_self" class="inform_link">Vogue</a> in the same way ever again.</p>			
						<div style="width: 300px; float: right">

															<ul class="related-list">
																														<li><a href="/The-Culture/Movies/2009/1212/A-Single-Man-movie-review">A Single Man: movie review</a></li>																																								
	
<li class="c-article">				
											
<a class="" href="/Business/Latest-News-Wires/2011/0908/Fashion-s-Night-Out-hopes-to-give-retail-sales-a-boost">Fashion's Night Out hopes to give retail sales a boost</a>
</li>
																																								<li>
												<a href="/tags/list_articles" >View all lists</a>
																							</li>
																											</ul>
							
